	dprr:hasNoteText "He persisted in his veto of the agrarian bill of Gracchus, and was deposed by vote of the assembly (Cic. Mil. 72; ND 1.106; Leg. 3.24; Brut. 95; Liv. Per. 58; Diod. 34-35.7.1; Vell. 2.2.3; Ascon. 72 C; Plut. TG 10-12, and 14-15; Flor. 2.2.5; Dio fr. 83, and 46.49.2; Auct. Vir. Ill. 64.4; Oros. 5.8.3; cf. FOR 2.11-12, 113f.)." .
